    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate with a clear focal point in **Corbin Carroll**, who leads our lineup with an elite 87.14 efficiency score. His matchup against Sean Burke is our most anticipated scenario; the combination of a favorable park and Burke\u2019s vulnerability to aggressive baserunning positions **Corbin Carroll** to capitalize on his elite sprint speed\u2014our primary target for category scarcity. Complementing him are **James Wood** (78.42) and **Mickey Moniak** (75.75), both of whom benefit significantly from facing Randy V\u00e1squez and Reynaldo L\u00f3pez, respectively. These matchups carry high projected SP skill advantages (19%), providing the offensive upside required to climb the standings in Roto. **Brice Turang** also remains a locked-in high-floor play (72.86) due to his leadoff spot and a positive park factor, stabilizing our daily stolen base floor.\n\nThe decision to bench **Alex Freeland** was razor-thin, as his 49.73 score fell just shy of the 50-point threshold required to crack the active roster. While **Alex Freeland** offers switch-hitting versatility, the optimizer ultimately preferred the higher-ceiling platoon advantages presented by **Vinnie Pasquantino** and **Trevor Story**. We are cautiously monitoring **Dalton Rushing**, whose 51.38 score is tethered to a 42% rain risk in his matchup against Landen Roupp. Should that game face significant delays, we may need to pivot to our bench depth. Meanwhile, **Seiya Suzuki** is a marginal start (51.64) due to the stiff challenge posed by Jes\u00fas Luzardo; his value today is almost entirely dependent on his ability to leverage the wind conditions, as the elite arm on the mound significantly caps his raw projection.",
